-- Pakistani stocks higher; rupee steady, o/n rates flat
-- 
-- Thu Oct 02, 2014 08:05AM EDT
-- None



KARACHI, Oct 2 (Reuters) - Pakistani shares ended higher for the third straight session on Thursday, led by institutional buying in some banking stocks.

The benchmark 100-share index of the Karachi Stock Exchange <.KSE> edged up 0.25 percent, or 74.97 points, at 30,071.58. "Institutional interest in select stocks resulted in the market closing above the 30,000 point level," said Samar Iqbal, a dealer at Topline Securities.  "Institutional interest was seen in National Bank of Pakistan <NBPK.KA> and Bank Alfalah Ltd <BAFL.KA>." Bank Alfalah rose 4.41 percent to 29.69 rupees, while National Bank of Pakistan closed up 0.49 percent at 61.12 rupees. The rupee <PKR=> ended almost steady at 102.55/102.65 against the dollar, compared with Wednesday's close of 102.55/102.60.